Detailed Description

The class Collection contains several utilities performing some basic collection operations (like union, intersection...).

static ICollection MathNet.Numerics.Collection.Inter ( ICollection  c1,
ICollection  c2 
) [static]

Returns a collection resulting from the mathematical intersection of c1 and c2.

Parameters:
c1 Should not be null.
c2 Should not be null.

The call is performed in O(c1.Count+c2.Count) and the intersection is built explicitly.

The resulting collection will not contain several identical elements.

Example: Inter({1;1;2;3},{0;1;1;3;4}) = {1;3}.
